was really a back door QE.

00:47:47.104 --> 00:47:48.770 align:middle line:84%
And then, of course,
at the end of 2012,

00:47:48.770 --> 00:47:52.200 align:middle line:84%
they initiated QE
three and four.

00:47:52.200 --> 00:47:55.200 align:middle line:84%
Abenomics, they started
talking about in 2012

00:47:55.200 --> 00:47:57.240 align:middle line:90%
and initiated right afterward.

00:47:57.240 --> 00:48:00.080 align:middle line:84%
And in Europe, they did
something called the LTRO, Long

00:48:00.080 --> 00:48:03.660 align:middle line:84%
Term Refinancing Operation,
which really meant

00:48:03.660 --> 00:48:05.420 align:middle line:84%
printing money and
giving it to the banks.

00:48:05.420 --> 00:48:08.590 align:middle line:84%
So then you really saw the
money printing go crazy.

00:48:08.590 --> 00:48:11.170 align:middle line:84%
That's when you've seen the
spike in the money supply.

00:48:11.170 --> 00:48:14.510 align:middle line:84%
